  "translations": {
    "en": "Sa'id ibn Jubayr said: So I left him and prepared for the next day. I went early at dawn, prayed the dawn prayer, then mentioned the hadith. He turned his face toward me and said: Listen to what I say: I heard the Messenger of God (may blessings be upon him and his family) say: If you were to know what you have in Ramadan you would increase your thanksgiving to God. On the first night, God forgave all the sins of my Nation, raised you by two million ranks, and built fifty cities for you.",
    "ur": "Sa'id ibn Jubayr said: So I left him and prepared for the next day. I went early at dawn, prayed the dawn prayer, then mentioned the hadith. He turned his face toward me and said: Listen to what I say: I heard the Messenger of God (may blessings be upon him and his family) say: If you were to know what you have in Ramadan you would increase your thanksgiving to God. On the first night, God forgave all the sins of my Nation, raised you by two million ranks, and built fifty cities for you.",
